description: Tumour Necrosis Factor binds to TNF Receptor 1 to mediate its effects.
Tumour Necrosis Factor binds to TNF Receptor 2, which is involved in signaling pathways.
Tumour Necrosis Factor has been implicated in the disease state of Rheumatoid Arthritis.
Tumour Necrosis Factor has been implicated in the disease state of Ankylosing Spondylitis.
Tumour Necrosis Factor has been implicated in the disease state of Crohn's Disease.
